original: Cronvall, Nils 0’scar Albin, tullförvaltare, Ronneby, f. 28/7/90 i Malmö av målarm. Axel C. o. Ellen Ljunggren. G. 17 m. Nellie Claussen. Barn: Marianne f. 22, Sven 28. — Stud:ex. v. Malmö h. a. 1. 09. Kammar skriv, i Landskrona t. 43, tullförvalt. i Köping 43-44, tf. tullkontr. i Landskrona 45, tullförvalt. i Ronneby sed. 46.
translated: Cronvall, Nils Oscar Albin was a customs administrator in Ronneby. He was born on July 28, 1890 in Malmö to the painter Axel C. and Ellen Ljunggren. He married Nellie Claussen in 1917 and they had two children: Marianne, born in 1922 and Sven, born in 1928. He completed high school at Malmö in 1909 and worked as a clerk in Landskrona until 1943 when he became a customs administrator in Köping. He served as an acting customs inspector in Landskrona in 1945 before becoming a customs administrator in Ronneby where he worked from 1946 onwards.
